[§551E‑36]  Stocks and bonds.  Unless the power of attorney otherwise provides, language in a power of attorney granting general authority with respect to stocks and bonds shall authorize the agent to:
     (1)  Buy, sell, and exchange stocks and bonds;
     (2)  Establish, continue, modify, or terminate an account with respect to stocks and bonds;
     (3)  Pledge stocks and bonds as security to borrow, pay, renew, or extend the time of payment of a debt of the principal;
     (4)  Receive certificates and other evidences of ownership with respect to stocks and bonds; and
     (5)  Exercise voting rights with respect to stocks and bonds in person or by proxy, enter into voting trusts, and consent to limitations on the right to vote. [L 2014, c 22, pt of §1]
